name: First Trust Vest U.S. Equity Buffer ETF - May
longDescription: To achieve its investment objectives, the ETF will under normal market conditions invest substantially all of its assets in FLexible EXchange Options ('FLEX Options') that reference the price return of the Underlying ETF. The investment objective of the Underlying ETF is to seek to provide investment results that, before expenses, correspond generally to the price and yield performance of the S&P 500 Index. The ETF seeks to provide unitholders with returns (before fees, expenses, taxes and, any changes to the CanadianU.S. dollar exchange rate) that match the price return of the SPDR SP 5 ETF Trust (the Underlying ETF) up to a predetermined upside cap of 17.
fulldescription: To achieve its investment objectives, the ETF will under normal market conditions invest substantially all of its assets in FLexible EXchange Options ('FLEX Options') that reference the price return of the Underlying ETF. The investment objective of the Underlying ETF is to seek to provide investment results that, before expenses, correspond generally to the price and yield performance of the S&P 500 Index. The ETF seeks to provide unitholders with returns (before fees, expenses, taxes and, any changes to the CanadianU.S. dollar exchange rate) that match the price return of the SPDR SP 5 ETF Trust (the Underlying ETF) up to a predetermined upside cap of 17.65 percent (before fees, expenses, taxes and, any changes to the CanadianU.S. dollar exchange rate), while providing a buffer against the first 1 percent (before fees, expenses and taxes and, any changes to the CanadianU.S. dollar exchange rate) of the decrease in market price of the Underlying ETF, over a period of approximately one year from the Monday following the third Friday of May of each year to on or about the third Friday of May of the following year (each, a Target Outcome Period).
